-- Prompt templates for the dev loop.
-- Each function takes structured data, returns a prompt string.
-- Prompts start at column 0 (dedent not yet implemented in multi-line strings).
-- JSON schema injection and validation handled by ai.prompt_structured via Protocols.

+pick_task = (truth ctx) {
"Pick the single highest-leverage task for lx development.

State: {truth.pass_count} tests pass, {truth.fail_count} fail, diagnose clean={truth.diag_clean}
Modified files: {truth.git_status}

Priorities (PRIORITIES.md):
{ctx.priorities}

Design opinion (OPINION.md):
{ctx.opinion}

Roadmap (unimplemented):
{ctx.roadmap}"
}

+worker = (ctx task) {
"{ctx.claude_md}

--- COLD START: agent/NEXT_PROMPT.md ---
{ctx.next_prompt}

--- YOUR TASK ---
{task.task}
Category: {task.category}
Acceptance: {task.acceptance}
Key files: {task.key_files}

CONSTRAINTS:
- Follow CLAUDE.md rules exactly
- Run just diagnose before finishing and fix all errors and warnings
- Run just test before finishing and fix all failures
- Do NOT modify any files in the agent/ directory
- Do NOT create git commits
- Stay focused on this single task, no scope creep"
}

+update_context = (ctx task v diff_stat stamp) {
"Update the lx project agent context files. Use ONLY the verified facts below.

VERIFIED FACTS (mechanical, not AI-claimed):
  Task completed: {task.task} [{task.category}]
  Tests passing: {v.pass_count}
  Tests failing: {v.fail_count}
  Diagnose clean: {v.diag_clean}
  Date: {stamp}

FILES CHANGED:
{diff_stat}

CURRENT NEXT_PROMPT.md:
{ctx.next_prompt}

CURRENT DEVLOG.md (recent):
{ctx.devlog}

The next_prompt field MUST state {v.pass_count} tests passing."
}
